org.chronos.chronodb.api.key

Interface TemporalKey

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TemporalKeyImpl

    public interface TemporalKey
    A TemporalKey is a QualifiedKey with additional temporal information.

    This class does not extend QualifiedKey due to problems with collection containment checks and the #equals(Object) method.

      • create

        static TemporalKey create(long timestamp,
                          QualifiedKey qualifiedKey)
        Creates a new TemporalKey.
        Parameters:
        timestamp - The timestamp to use in the new temporal key. Must not be negative.
        qualifiedKey - The qualified key to read data from for the new temporal key. Data will be copied, the qualified key will not be modified. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The newly created temporal key. Never null.

      • toQualifiedKey

        QualifiedKey toQualifiedKey()
        Returns a representation of this TemporalKey as a QualifiedKey.

        Note that a QualifiedKey contains less data than a TemporalKey. Two different temporal keys may therefore produce two equal qualified keys.

        Returns:
        The qualified key representation of this temporal key. Never null.
